Singer Abigail has joined Sony Music Entertainment. Abigail, a singer-songwriter who sings in Kiswahili, English and French, said she felt blessed to be one of the performing female artists to represent Africa on a major label. "This is a dream come true, a manifestation of sorts and the constant pursuit to be better each day," she said. "It is a testament to my faith and hard work. The world is about to get the Abigail experience." Abigail is a Unicef Youth Advocate for Mental Health and Gender-Based Violence and has been hosted on the popular American show. Welcoming her to a leading global music label, Sony Music East Africa head Christine ‘Seven’ Mosha said Abigail is a multi-faceted artiste with a powerful voice, look and energy that will captivate audiences.